
YANGDUMP -- A Compiler for the YANG data modeling language
===========================================================

Copyright (c) 2008, Andy Bierman

See the file "COPYING" for information on usage and redistribution
of this file, and for a DISCLAIMER OF ALL WARRANTIES.

This software comprises:

 - a binary linux program called 'yangdump'
 - documentation pages
 - a set of freely available YANG modules 

Some of the YANG modules includes with this software were
generated with the smidump program, available at:

 http://www.ibr.cs.tu-bs.de/projects/libsmi/

WARNING
=======

This version of yangdump implements the YANG language specification
as defined in:

http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-bjorklund-netconf-yang-02.txt

Future versions of yangdump may not maintain full compatibility with
this Internet Draft.

IMPORTANT INSTALLATION NOTE
===========================

  **************************************************************
  *                                                            *
  *  This program will not function unless the yangdump.ncx    *
  *  and ncxtypes.ncx files are available in the module path.  *
  *  These files are used for CLI and config file processing.  *
  *                                                            *
  **************************************************************

MANIFEST
========

README					this file
COPYING					the yangdump license terms
ChangeLog				a summary of changes to each release
yangdump                                binary executable program
yangdump.1                              man page for yangdump (groff format)
yangdump-man.html                       man page for yangdump (HTML format)
modules.tar.gz                          YANG data models in modules/... 


INSTALLATION
============

 1) Copy the file 'yangdump' to a directory within your shell's
    search path for executables, such as /usr/bin or /usr/local/bin.
    You will need to choose a different location if you do not
    have root priveleges.

     >> cp yanto /usr/local/bin

 2) Unzip the modules.tar.gz file

     >>  gunzip modules.tar.gz

 3) Untar the modules directory somewhere in the module search
    path for yangdump.  A directory tree called 'modules' will
    be created.

     >> tar xvf modules.tar <target-dir>

    - The default locations searched by yangdump for modules:
  
       -  current directory
       -  $HOME/modules
       - /usr/share/yang/modules

   - If the YANG_HOME or YANG_INSTALL environment variables
     is set, then yangdump will also look for modules there:

       - $YANG_HOME/modules
       - $YANG_INSTALL/modules

 4) create a yangdump config file, if desired.
    The default config file checked by yangdump is:

       - /etc/yangdump.conf

    This default can be overridden with the --config parameter.

 5) View the man page for more details on usage

   - yangdump-man.html

  OR

  - man ./yangdump.1
